id: pmc-l9z0
title: Published package sourcemaps point to missing source files
description: "Add inlineSources: true to tsconfig.json so dist/.js.map files embed TypeScript source content. V8 uses the embedded sourcesContent and stops warning about missing .ts files when the package is installed without the src/ directory."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 2
tags[3]: packaging,sourcemaps,tsconfig
created_at: "2026-05-24T00:04:42.271Z"
updated_at: "2026-05-24T00:09:06.069Z"
deadline: "2026-05-24T00:00:00.000Z"
author: claude
estimated_minutes: 30
acceptance_criteria: "inlineSources: true added to tsconfig.json; dist rebuilt; npm run release:check passes; clean pm install no longer emits sourcemap warnings; GitHub issue #4 closed"
release: Unreleased
severity: high
resolution: "Added inlineSources: true to tsconfig.json; rebuilt dist; sourcesContent embedded in all .js.map files."
expected_result: No V8 sourcemap warnings; .js.map files contain sourcesContent.
actual_result: "inlineSources: true added; dist rebuilt; sourcesContent verified in all .js.map; 18/18 tests pass; npm run release:check passes."
